citation: Proclamation under the Criminal Code Amendment (Child Exploitation) Act 2005 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Criminal Code Amendment (Child Exploitation) Act 2005

I, the Administrator in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2 of the Criminal Code Amendment (Child Exploitation) Act 2005 fix 1 August 2005 as the day on which that Act commences.

11 July 2005

E. C. CRAWFORD

Administrator

By His Excellency's Command,

JUDY JACKSON

Minister for Justice and Industrial Relations

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 20 July 2005

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Justice.
